Release Notes
Optimized Default Settings Impact
Solana 4-Hour Timeframe:

Before (ATR: 10, Factor: 3.0): Profit Factor 1.4
After (ATR: 16, Factor: 3.11): Profit Factor 1.6+ ✅
Improvement: +14% profit factor, fewer whipsaws, better drawdown control

Solana 12-Hour Timeframe:

Optimized Settings: Profit Factor 2.0+ ✅
Win Rate: ~45%
Avg Win/Loss: ~3.5:1
Max Drawdown: ~18%

Why It Works:

Longer ATR (16 vs 10) = smoother volatility calculation, less noise sensitivity
Higher Factor (3.11 vs 3.0) = wider bands, requires stronger momentum to flip
Result: ~30% fewer false signals, higher quality entries, better risk-reward
Dec 11, 2025
Release Notes
Hash Supertrend — Regime-Based Trend Framework

Purpose
Hash Supertrend is a systematic trend-following framework built around the classic Supertrend structure, enhanced with adaptive volatility settings, session filters, and a professional visual system designed to make regime transitions clear. The goal is to help operators interpret directional bias using a consistent volatility-adjusted trend model.

Conceptual Framework

The engine is based on ATR-derived price bands that define directional bias:

When price closes above the upper band, the model shifts into a bullish regime.

When price closes below the lower band, the model shifts into a bearish regime.



ATR length controls how quickly volatility reacts to new information, while the multiplier determines how far price must extend before a directional change is recognized. Lower values increase responsiveness; higher values emphasize stability.

This implementation focuses on clarity of regime definition, allowing operators to evaluate trend conditions without relying on secondary indicators.

Execution Logic (High-Level)
A position is opened or reversed only when the Supertrend direction changes:

Bullish Flip → Long entry

Bearish Flip → Short entry


This produces a single-position, one-direction-at-a-time workflow suitable for discretionary or systematic execution. Time filters can be enabled to restrict trading to defined sessions, which may be helpful for assets with concentrated liquidity patterns.

Visual System
To support rapid regime identification, the script uses:

Adaptive fluorescent color spectrum to distinguish bullish and bearish states

Optional glow effect to highlight trend transitions

Trend zone fill between price and the Supertrend line to visualize directional structure

Entry markers for clear execution reference

These visuals do not influence the strategy logic and are provided solely for interpretive clarity.



Inputs
ATR Length
Controls volatility lookback. Shorter values respond faster; longer values reduce noise.

Factor (ATR Multiplier)
Defines how much directional extension is required for a trend flip.

Time Filter (Optional)
Restricts entries to specific hours. Operators trading around liquidity windows or avoiding overnight conditions may enable this.

Visual Controls
Allow customization of color intensity, glow effects, and trend zone behavior.

Intended Use
The framework is applicable across liquid markets including crypto, FX, equities, and indices.
It is structurally best suited to directional or trending environments.
Operators may use alerts to integrate the signals into systematic workflows.

Limitations

Like all trend-based systems, performance may degrade in range-bound or low-volatility environments.

Users should validate settings for their instrument and timeframe before applying the strategy to live workflows.



For educational discussion only. Not financial advice.
